God of War, Kuan Ti.

00:30:41.880 --> 00:30:48.255 align:middle line:90%


00:30:48.255 --> 00:30:52.630 align:middle line:10%
Kuan Ti taught him the methods
of celestial martial arts

00:30:52.630 --> 00:30:57.240 align:middle line:10%
and the alchemical secret
of the golden embryo.

00:30:57.240 --> 00:30:59.590 align:middle line:84%
Chang San-Feng
combined these lessons

00:30:59.590 --> 00:31:02.920 align:middle line:84%
with a style of fighting based
on the movements he observed

00:31:02.920 --> 00:31:04.400 align:middle line:90%
of the crane and the snake.

00:31:04.400 --> 00:31:11.440 align:middle line:90%


00:31:11.440 --> 00:31:14.260 align:middle line:84%
This method relies
upon internal power,

00:31:14.260 --> 00:31:17.000 align:middle line:84%
or chi, and is based
on the principal that

00:31:17.000 --> 00:31:20.740 align:middle line:84%
yielding overcomes aggression,
and softness overpowers

00:31:20.740 --> 00:31:21.240 align:middle line:90%
hardness.

00:31:21.240 --> 00:31:25.910 align:middle line:90%


00:31:25.910 --> 00:31:29.210 align:middle line:84%
Chang San-Feng called
it Tai Chi Chuan,

00:31:29.210 --> 00:31:36.926 align:middle line:90%
or "the supreme, ultimate fist."

00:31:36.926 --> 00:31:39.330 align:middle line:84%
The highest level
